parameters:
"Ready for your first task?

First, let's familiarize you with the mining process. Try mining a dirt block by clicking and holding the left mouse button while hovering over one. If the block is not highlighted, it's too far away from you. 

You can move using WASD controls or the Arrow Keys.
"

"Good work! You've mined your first block!

You can see how many blocks you've collected by pressing the 'i' key. Why don't you give it a try?"

"From this menu, you can see all of the blocks that you've collected this run. When you return to your ship, these will be processed into the minerals that compose them. Press 'i' again to close this menu."

"This mining sure is going slowly though, and this is just dirt! We're going to want to upgrade this Rusty Old Drill if we want to start mining tougher materials. We can upgrade it to a Fiberglass Drill back at the Factory. However, we're going to need some minerals first.

It will take 10,000 grams of Silica, and 1,000 grams of Alumina to afford that upgrade. While some of those materials can be found in dirt, we're going to find much more Silica in sand, and we're likely to find Alumina in Clay. There's a river to the right of here, maybe we can find what we're looking for there!

Press Z to close this display"

"Current Objective: 
Find and mine Sand and Clay"

"Good job! You've found sand!

Sand is largely composed of Silica. 10 blocks of Sand should provide enough Silica to upgrade your drill.

Press Z to close this message"

"Current Objectives: 
Collect 10 Sand blocks.
Collect 5 Clay blocks."

"Good job! You've found clay!

Clay is composed of Silica, Alumina, and Magnesia. 5 blocks of Clay should provide enough Alumina to upgrade your drill.

Press Z to close this message"

"Current Objectives: 
Collect 10 Sand blocks.
Collect 5 Clay blocks."

"This should be enough materials! Let's return to the ship for now.

Press Z to close this message"

"I don't think we're quite ready to return to the ship. 

Press Z to close this message.
"

parameters:
"Oh no! You were not careful in your mining practices and you have created an oil spill. This will set back our restoration efforts in a big way, and will take a lot of resources to clean up. 
*Your resources are halved and you earned nothing today*

Press Z to continue"

"Up until now, we have relied on fossil fuels found in Shale to power our generators. However, this is not sustainable in the long term. We will need to upgrade our factories to use clean energy such as solar and wind, which will require the use of some new materials. Because this location is on a tectonic plate boundary, we're much likely to find some of the more rare metals we need!

Most of the crust is made of silica because it's less dense than most metals in magma so it rises to the surface and solidifies, but near tectonic plate boundaries like these, denser magma containing heavy metals can be brought to the surface through volcanic activity. 
"

"We should look for Cobalt and Copper so that we can upgrade our equipment and factories. These metals are often found together near tectonic plate boundaries. We should also avoid mining shale, so we don't release trapped carbon and pollutants into the environment.

While these minerals will also be useful in generating batteries, which we will need for storing energy as we transition away from our use of fossil fuels to cleaner energy sources, it is important to be mindful that harvesting these metals still has an environmental impact as well. Restoring the Earth will require a careful balance of using what we need to progress while transitioning to fully sustainable practices. Consider as you complete your mission other possibilities for storing energy."

"Objective:
Mine 10 Cobalt.
Mine 10 Copper-containing deposits.
Mine no more than 5 Shale."

"You've found Chalcopyrite! This is a copper-iron-sulfide mineral, and the most abundant Copper ore on Earth. This will make a great source of copper.

Press Z to close this message."

"You've found Cobalt! This is a ferromagnetic metal used in batteries and industrial magnets.

Press Z to close this message."

"Careful! If you keep mining Shale you may cause an oil spill!

Press Z to close this message."

"This should be enough to upgrade our equipment! You can head back to the factory or stay and collect more.

Press Z to close this message."

inlineCode: * Update the coordinates in the basisObject basis.
* It uses the basisObject coordinates from the previous frame.
* This way, the sticker can move relatively to it and still
// Save initial values to avoid calculus and rounding errors
* Copy the coordinates to use it the next frame.
* This method is also called by children to ensure
// If the behavior on the basis object has a different name,
// the objects will still follow their basis objects
// Follow parents 1st to avoid frame delays
object.setX(basisObject.getCenterXInScene() + object.getX() - object.getCenterXInScene() + deltaX * Math.cos(angle) + deltaY * Math.sin(angle));
object.setY(basisObject.getCenterYInScene() + object.getY() - object.getCenterYInScene() - deltaX * Math.sin(angle) + deltaY * Math.cos(angle));
// Unproportional dimensions changes won't work as expected
// if the object angle is not null but nothing more can be done
// because there is no full affine transformation on objects.

events.comment:
Create one background instance for of each state.
Only the instance for the current state is shown.
Place the label over the backgrounds.
Show the right background accordingly to the new state.

Children instances must be resized when the button size change:
- backgrounds for each state are resized to take the full dimensions of the button
- the label is put back at the center of the button

The scale is set back to 1 because it means that the parent instance has the same dimensions as the union of its children instances.
